
# 🛡️ VHDL Digital Safe Project
### Target Hardware: Nexys A7-50T (Artix-7)

This project implements a secure 4-digit digital safe using VHDL. It features a modular design including debounced button inputs, a live-preview display driver, and a persistent register-based memory system.

---

## 🚀 Features
- **Live Preview:** View switch changes on the display in real-time before saving.
- **Decimal Point Cursor:** Indicates which of the 4 digits is currently being edited.
- **Robust Debouncing:** Filters mechanical noise for precise button control.
- **Security Logic:** Green LED for 'Access Granted' (PIN 1234), Red LED for 'Locked'.
- **Hexadecimal Support:** Allows digits from 0-F for enhanced security.

---

## 🎮 Controls
| Input | Action |
| :--- | :--- |
| **BTNU** | 🔄 System Reset (Wipes current entry) |
| **BTNL / BTNR** | ↔️ Move Cursor Left/Right (Decimal Point) |
| **BTND** | 💾 Save Switch Value to Current Position |
| **SW [3:0]** | 🔢 Set Hex Value (0-F) for the selected digit |

